    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@Haroenv Ah, I'll have a look into those options then, just a last question:\r\n\r\nI have a `<Configure />` widget like the following below:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n<Configure \r\n  hitsPerPage={10} \r\n  facetFilters={filters}\r\n  numericFilters={numericFilters}\r\n  attributesToRetrieve={[ 'name', 'pet_type']}\r\n/>\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd I would like to dynamically search on the facet values in React with the configure widget on submitting a button e.g. `['pet_type:dog'], ['pet_type:cat'], ['pet_type:fish']`.\r\n\r\nIs there an example of this in action? I've searched the Algolia documentation for this for days on end for this example to no avail.",
